						               													<description>Saloon Showdown is an unsettled boardgame where up to 7 gunslingers of all ages will try to collect the bounties on the heads of others, challenging each others in epic duels, truels and Mexican standoff!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Reflexes and speed of thought will determine the most skillful gunslinger... but there are also other, more devious ways to win!&amp;#10;&amp;#10;...Do you feel lucky?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Starting from the player on the left of the dealer, the game proceeds clockwise in turns. In their turn each player can choose 1 of this actions: draw a card, cash the loot (discard some type of cards to earn dollars) or threaten somebody.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Threatening someone with a gun starts a brief &amp;quot;bluff or not&amp;quot; phase, which can lead to the heart of the game: the Duel.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In the Duel, two players must exchange their cards and be the quicker to shoot the other correctly, by guessing 3 things:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     the color of the gun to take;&amp;#10;     the zone of the body to hit;&amp;#10;     the sound of the gunshot.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The correct information is the one that is most present on the cards in front of the player.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In the game there are also two variants of the Duel, which involve 3 players (Truel) or up to 5 (Mexican Standoff).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;By playing cards and winning Duels, you earn (or steal) money.&amp;#10;The game ends when a player has $130 on his Loot zone, or when he has 3 Wound tokens (which you get by losing Duels).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description from the designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
